1
00:00:14,547 --> 00:00:16,014
Hello, Michele.

2
00:00:16,082 --> 00:00:17,777
Roberto.

3
00:00:17,851 --> 00:00:19,751
- Come in.
- Give it to me please.

4
00:00:21,288 --> 00:00:23,222
Some water please, Rita.

5
00:00:25,492 --> 00:00:27,426
How's Elsa?

6
00:00:27,494 --> 00:00:29,792
Fine. And Giovanna?

7
00:00:29,863 --> 00:00:31,455
Fine.

8
00:00:35,302 --> 00:00:38,601
Listen, Roberto.

9
00:00:41,708 --> 00:00:44,176
I know your choices

10
00:00:44,244 --> 00:00:46,906
were imposed by necessity

11
00:00:46,980 --> 00:00:49,847
and maybe our tempers

12
00:00:49,916 --> 00:00:51,213
got the better of us.

13
00:00:52,252 --> 00:00:53,776
And so...

14
00:00:57,190 --> 00:01:00,353
perhaps we should reconsider
our relationship.

15
00:01:01,594 --> 00:01:04,119
- Here's the water.
- Thank you.

16
00:01:13,406 --> 00:01:15,931
I certainly didn't expect
to hear this.

17
00:01:16,009 --> 00:01:18,944
Life's full of surprises.

18
00:01:24,584 --> 00:01:28,281
Of course,
now the situation's a bit different.

19
00:01:28,355 --> 00:01:30,915
And the new organization...

20
00:01:30,991 --> 00:01:32,925
you know that Morelli's

21
00:01:32,993 --> 00:01:36,258
changing the structure completely.

22
00:01:36,329 --> 00:01:39,025
We're aiming

23
00:01:39,099 --> 00:01:41,363
for compactness

24
00:01:41,434 --> 00:01:43,902
and we have to be united

25
00:01:43,970 --> 00:01:46,530
and firm on everything.

26
00:01:46,606 --> 00:01:49,234
You should see yourself.

27
00:01:51,144 --> 00:01:53,510
You're terrified.

28
00:01:53,580 --> 00:01:55,912
Don't hide behind Morelli.

29
00:01:55,982 --> 00:01:57,643
It's you.

30
00:01:57,717 --> 00:02:00,515
It's you who's acting
like a piece of shit and you know it.

31
00:02:00,587 --> 00:02:02,418
I'm in deep shit,

32
00:02:02,489 --> 00:02:04,787
but you really are
a piece of shit

33
00:02:04,858 --> 00:02:06,348
and I don't even know
why the fuck I came!

34
00:02:06,426 --> 00:02:09,327
Now I recognize it.
I recognize

35
00:02:09,396 --> 00:02:11,193
the old dick-head.

36
00:02:11,264 --> 00:02:14,290
- You had me fooled for a second.
- Now you've pissed me off!

37
00:02:27,213 --> 00:02:29,010
Michele?

38
00:02:39,893 --> 00:02:41,292
Michele.

39
00:03:44,324 --> 00:03:46,383
Wait, Luciano.

40
00:03:59,305 --> 00:04:01,296
Careful.

41
00:04:01,374 --> 00:04:04,639
Watch out for the door.

42
00:04:04,711 --> 00:04:07,407
Let's put this in the middle.
Then we'll see.

43
00:04:07,480 --> 00:04:10,005
Excuse me, wait a second.
Can I go through?

44
00:04:10,083 --> 00:04:12,244
Luciano, go back!

45
00:04:14,154 --> 00:04:16,588
Let's find a place
for it right now.

46
00:04:16,656 --> 00:04:19,124
Elsa, it'll never fit.
There's no room.

47
00:04:19,192 --> 00:04:21,285
Should we sell this one too?

48
00:04:21,361 --> 00:04:23,659
Will you please make
up your minds?

49
00:04:23,730 --> 00:04:26,756
- Yes.
- Okay. Let me through.

50
00:04:26,833 --> 00:04:29,358
Luciano, go back again.

51
00:04:44,184 --> 00:04:46,846
Alice called earlier.
She told me to give you a kiss.

52
00:04:48,788 --> 00:04:51,052
She doesn't call me, does she?

53
00:04:51,124 --> 00:04:53,149
You could call her.

54
00:05:11,778 --> 00:05:14,474
Maybe with earplugs we'd be able
to sleep. What do you think?

55
00:05:19,752 --> 00:05:22,346
Remember that house
at Santarém?

56
00:05:22,422 --> 00:05:24,788
We got there late at night,

57
00:05:24,857 --> 00:05:27,587
then the next morning
we took a boat

58
00:05:27,660 --> 00:05:29,491
and the boatman said,

59
00:05:29,562 --> 00:05:31,962
"You're staying there.

60
00:05:32,031 --> 00:05:35,762
This house will fall
apart soon." Remember?

61
00:05:35,835 --> 00:05:39,635
I wonder if it's still standing
or if it's just rubble.

62
00:05:39,706 --> 00:05:42,971
Brazil. What a wonderful trip.

63
00:05:46,479 --> 00:05:48,504
Elsa...

64
00:05:51,618 --> 00:05:54,143
we'll make this place nice,
you'll see.

65
00:06:08,234 --> 00:06:11,067
Why is this taking
longer than yesterday?

66
00:06:11,137 --> 00:06:13,503
This room's bigger.

67
00:06:13,573 --> 00:06:16,440
Well, we don't have
anything else to do.

68
00:06:16,509 --> 00:06:19,171
The longer it takes,
the better.

69
00:06:19,245 --> 00:06:21,543
But the money's
the same, Luciano.

70
00:06:21,614 --> 00:06:25,050
- Sorry, but l...
- He's not talking about that.

71
00:06:25,118 --> 00:06:28,918
Luciano never talks about money,
don't worry. Seriously.

72
00:06:37,930 --> 00:06:41,263
This kitchen's kind of small.
And dark, too.

73
00:06:41,334 --> 00:06:45,031
Why the hell didn't they make
an opening in this wall?

74
00:06:45,104 --> 00:06:48,096
We could put a table there.
It'd be nicer, wouldn't it?

75
00:06:48,174 --> 00:06:51,507
You know, Mr. Oliveri,
that's a great idea.

76
00:06:52,679 --> 00:06:54,670
Eh, Luciano?
What's to stop us?

77
00:06:54,747 --> 00:06:58,478
- What do you want to do?
- We're deciding whether to make a hole.

78
00:06:58,551 --> 00:07:00,746
It might be
a load-bearing wall.

79
00:07:00,820 --> 00:07:04,085
- You think so?
- Load-bearing.

80
00:07:05,825 --> 00:07:08,885
- It's about 10cm thick.
- No more than that.

81
00:07:08,961 --> 00:07:11,828
- What if there are pipes?
- Going where, Luciano?

82
00:07:11,898 --> 00:07:14,423
The bathroom's
on the other side.

83
00:07:14,500 --> 00:07:17,469
Well, maybe we should
ask the owner.

84
00:07:17,537 --> 00:07:19,767
For a permit?
Well, in that case...

85
00:07:19,839 --> 00:07:22,103
Most of the time,
if they're improvements...

86
00:07:26,145 --> 00:07:27,203
It isn't load-bearing.

87
00:07:29,816 --> 00:07:32,751
This part's still
at an intermediate stage

88
00:07:32,819 --> 00:07:35,788
and here there's just a sinopia.

89
00:07:35,855 --> 00:07:39,222
Who knows if the central
part was finished?

90
00:07:40,927 --> 00:07:43,487
I wonder what the face is like.

91
00:07:43,563 --> 00:07:46,157
Girls, I'm too curious.

92
00:07:46,232 --> 00:07:49,099
Don't know about you,
but I'm staying late.

93
00:07:49,168 --> 00:07:52,467
Then I'll stay too.
I just have to make a phone call.

94
00:07:52,538 --> 00:07:56,269
Lucky you.
I don't even have to bother.

95
00:07:56,342 --> 00:07:58,469
Sandra, I can't stay
this evening.

96
00:07:58,544 --> 00:08:01,570
Okay. Next time.

97
00:08:01,647 --> 00:08:04,138
There'll soon
be another chance.

98
00:08:04,217 --> 00:08:07,516
Actually, I think
I'll have to stop coming.

99
00:08:07,587 --> 00:08:10,317
What are you
talking about, Elsa?

100
00:08:10,390 --> 00:08:12,290
Are you kidding?

101
00:08:14,193 --> 00:08:17,185
It's a difficult situation.
I'll explain some other time.

102
00:08:29,409 --> 00:08:32,207
- Good evening.
- Good evening to you.

103
00:08:32,278 --> 00:08:34,178
Almost finished?

104
00:08:34,247 --> 00:08:35,805
We need another day.

105
00:08:35,882 --> 00:08:38,612
- I know it's a nuisance.
- No, not at all.

106
00:08:38,684 --> 00:08:40,618
What floor are you working on?

107
00:08:40,686 --> 00:08:42,381
The third.
Will you excuse me?

108
00:08:42,455 --> 00:08:45,618
- Oh, the third one.
- Goodbye.

109
00:08:47,760 --> 00:08:49,421
- Good evening, ma'am.
- Good evening.

110
00:08:49,495 --> 00:08:51,429
- Wait, let me help you.
- Thank you.

111
00:08:51,497 --> 00:08:54,933
- Hi, how are you? Tired?
- So-so.

112
00:08:58,504 --> 00:09:00,597
- What about you?
- Fine.

113
00:09:00,673 --> 00:09:02,732
Vito and Luciano are
real professionals.

114
00:09:02,809 --> 00:09:04,800
You're too nice!

115
00:09:06,145 --> 00:09:08,705
- Good evening.
- Good evening.

116
00:09:13,853 --> 00:09:15,912
Whose idea was it?

117
00:09:15,988 --> 00:09:18,548
It won't stay like this,
it needs more work.

118
00:09:20,927 --> 00:09:22,986
Well, we can put a shelf here.

119
00:09:23,062 --> 00:09:25,690
There you go!
I knew the lady would like it!

120
00:09:25,765 --> 00:09:28,427
Fortunately.

121
00:09:28,701 --> 00:09:30,669
For example, I've never done

122
00:09:30,736 --> 00:09:33,466
wallpapering or plastering.

123
00:09:34,774 --> 00:09:37,004
Thanks.

124
00:09:37,076 --> 00:09:39,169
Anyway... thank you...

125
00:09:39,245 --> 00:09:41,679
this counts as skills

126
00:09:41,747 --> 00:09:43,874
down at the job center.

127
00:09:43,950 --> 00:09:45,781
What do you mean?

128
00:09:45,852 --> 00:09:48,980
I'm registered
at the employment agency, right?

129
00:09:49,055 --> 00:09:51,387
But while I'm waiting for work,

130
00:09:51,457 --> 00:09:54,187
I do the job center courses.

131
00:09:54,260 --> 00:09:57,252
They help us not to give up
or get depressed.

132
00:09:57,330 --> 00:10:00,595
Every once in a while,
they even find you a job.

133
00:10:00,666 --> 00:10:04,534
There are lots of us.
It's like going to school.

134
00:10:04,604 --> 00:10:08,096
There are the troublemakers, the ones
who come once and never come back.

135
00:10:08,174 --> 00:10:10,938
They lie to their wives
and go to the beach instead.

136
00:10:11,010 --> 00:10:14,173
There are also managers,
but they do separate courses.

137
00:10:14,247 --> 00:10:16,681
Everyone has their own skills.

138
00:10:16,749 --> 00:10:18,216
How can you do anything else?

139
00:10:18,284 --> 00:10:21,481
Well, we all have
other skills too.

140
00:10:21,554 --> 00:10:24,079
Somehow you learn
what they are.

141
00:10:24,156 --> 00:10:27,717
You could be a welder,
but you might be good at cooking too,

142
00:10:27,793 --> 00:10:29,454
so you find work in a restaurant.

143
00:10:29,529 --> 00:10:32,930
If I could cook like you, ma'am,
I'd have found a job ages ago.

144
00:10:32,999 --> 00:10:34,728
This pasta is wonderful.

145
00:10:34,800 --> 00:10:37,894
My compliments. Very good.

146
00:10:37,970 --> 00:10:41,838
- Don't overdo it. Is it really good?
- Yes. Delicious.

147
00:10:41,908 --> 00:10:43,842
See you tomorrow then?

148
00:10:43,910 --> 00:10:45,502
Okay, Mr. Oliveri. Thanks.

149
00:10:45,578 --> 00:10:48,012
Sorry, sir.

150
00:10:48,080 --> 00:10:50,071
This is a bit embarrassing.

151
00:10:50,149 --> 00:10:53,243
Could you advance us 100 euros?

152
00:10:53,319 --> 00:10:56,220
Of course, Vito.
I'll be right back.

153
00:10:56,289 --> 00:10:58,052
Thank you.

154
00:11:02,428 --> 00:11:04,988
Elsa,

155
00:11:05,064 --> 00:11:07,726
do you have 100 euros for Vito?

156
00:11:07,800 --> 00:11:09,563
He asked me for an advance.

157
00:11:09,635 --> 00:11:13,196
Yes, sure, in my purse there.

158
00:11:26,285 --> 00:11:28,810
- Here you go.
- Thanks, sir.

159
00:11:28,888 --> 00:11:32,221
- Good night.
- Good night to both of you.

160
00:11:39,465 --> 00:11:41,695
Let me do it.

161
00:11:44,503 --> 00:11:46,494
Listen, Michele,
I was thinking.

162
00:11:46,572 --> 00:11:49,268
Since you aren't getting
many interviews

163
00:11:49,342 --> 00:11:51,606
and everything's
at a standstill...

164
00:11:51,677 --> 00:11:54,544
We decided that
I'd take care of moving,

165
00:11:54,614 --> 00:11:56,309
of the house,
doing work here.

166
00:11:56,382 --> 00:11:58,407
- I know, that's what we said.
- So?

167
00:11:58,484 --> 00:12:01,214
Maybe in the meantime,

168
00:12:01,287 --> 00:12:03,721
these courses for managers
that Vito mentioned,

169
00:12:03,789 --> 00:12:06,952
might be a good way for you
to meet other people,

170
00:12:07,026 --> 00:12:09,722
- talk to them.
- We just had dinner with two people

171
00:12:09,795 --> 00:12:11,160
and talked to them, didn't we?

172
00:12:11,230 --> 00:12:13,164
We're all in the same boat,
aren't we?

173
00:12:13,232 --> 00:12:14,563
No, I'm sorry. No.

174
00:12:14,634 --> 00:12:16,898
Sure, they're nice and kind,
whatever you want,

175
00:12:16,969 --> 00:12:18,698
but they used to be
your ex-employees.

176
00:12:18,771 --> 00:12:21,763
It doesn't make much difference
for them to be cooks or laborers,

177
00:12:21,841 --> 00:12:23,433
but it does for you, damn it!

178
00:12:23,509 --> 00:12:25,739
You don't go out anymore.
You don't see anybody anymore.

179
00:12:25,811 --> 00:12:27,210
How do you see it then?

180
00:12:27,279 --> 00:12:29,804
You suggest I go and take a course
for unemployed managers?

181
00:12:29,882 --> 00:12:31,611
Is that how you see it?

182
00:12:42,662 --> 00:12:44,892
I've had another job offer,
as secretary

183
00:12:44,964 --> 00:12:47,228
in a naval brokers' office

184
00:12:47,299 --> 00:12:49,733
from 6:00 p.m. to 10:30 p.m.

185
00:12:49,802 --> 00:12:52,965
They pay well and I can still keep
the call center job.

186
00:12:53,039 --> 00:12:55,303
And what about
your restoring work?

187
00:12:55,374 --> 00:12:58,901
How can you even think
I can keep that on?!

188
00:13:19,297 --> 00:13:21,231
When a fax or email arrives,

189
00:13:21,299 --> 00:13:23,597
all you have to do is
advise whoever's on duty.

190
00:13:23,668 --> 00:13:25,363
If they ask you
to take it to them, do it,

191
00:13:25,436 --> 00:13:27,461
otherwise put it
with the incoming mail.

192
00:13:27,538 --> 00:13:29,472
Then there's the telephone.

193
00:13:29,540 --> 00:13:32,100
If it rings at this hour, 90% of the time
you'll have to speak English.

194
00:13:32,176 --> 00:13:33,803
But you don't have problem, right?

195
00:13:33,878 --> 00:13:35,812
No problem at all.

196
00:13:35,880 --> 00:13:37,905
I'm available to help
you with anything.

197
00:13:37,982 --> 00:13:39,609
I'm just pregnant, not sick.

198
00:13:39,684 --> 00:13:41,413
Call whenever you want, okay?

199
00:13:41,486 --> 00:13:45,115
For example, this is a draft
of the Hong Kong contract.

200
00:13:45,189 --> 00:13:47,123
We have to notify Salviati
right away.

201
00:13:47,191 --> 00:13:49,625
He's the agent on duty
in the evening.

202
00:13:49,694 --> 00:13:51,628
- Why don't you call him?
- Me?

203
00:13:51,696 --> 00:13:54,358
Yes. Dial extension 3-2-5.

204
00:13:55,433 --> 00:13:57,230
- 3-2-5.
- Perfect.

205
00:13:57,301 --> 00:13:58,928
- Salviati?
- Salviati.

206
00:13:59,003 --> 00:14:00,937
I'm making a hot drink.
Would you like something?

207
00:14:01,005 --> 00:14:03,439
- Yes, a coffee, thanks.
- One for me too, thanks.

208
00:14:03,508 --> 00:14:05,635
Oh, I apologize,
I didn't hear you answer.

209
00:14:05,710 --> 00:14:08,406
- This is not Cristina.
- No, I'm her substitute,

210
00:14:08,479 --> 00:14:10,913
- but I start tomorrow.
- Oh, yes! Because of the baby.

211
00:14:10,982 --> 00:14:14,383
- Well, good luck then.
- Thanks, good luck to you too.

212
00:14:14,452 --> 00:14:17,046
- Talk to you later.
- Okay.

213
00:14:26,264 --> 00:14:28,289
- Yes?
- Salviati speaking.

214
00:14:28,366 --> 00:14:31,529
- How may I help you?
- Did you need anything when you called?

215
00:14:31,602 --> 00:14:32,967
Oh yes,

216
00:14:33,037 --> 00:14:35,631
the draft of the Hong Kong
contract has arrived.

217
00:14:35,707 --> 00:14:38,198
Yes, good. I'll check it later.

218
00:14:38,276 --> 00:14:41,370
- Keep it there, please.
- Of course. That's fine, sir.

219
00:14:41,446 --> 00:14:44,108
How stupid of me.

220
00:14:49,020 --> 00:14:51,682
- Here. How many sugars?
- One.

221
00:14:53,458 --> 00:14:55,392
- You answer. It'll be Salviati.
- Me?

222
00:14:55,460 --> 00:14:57,291
Again?

223
00:14:57,361 --> 00:14:58,953
- Yes?
- It's me again.

224
00:14:59,030 --> 00:15:01,225
You didn't tell me your name.

225
00:15:01,299 --> 00:15:03,824
- Elsa.
- Thank you, Elsa.

226
00:15:03,901 --> 00:15:06,028
You're welcome.
Good evening.

227
00:15:08,106 --> 00:15:11,075
Thanks.

228
00:15:11,142 --> 00:15:13,007
...an estimate since
the job will last more.

229
00:15:13,077 --> 00:15:15,637
- Hi. Good evening, Vito.
- Good evening, ma'am.

230
00:15:15,713 --> 00:15:18,409
I'm sorry it's so late.
We're almost done.

231
00:15:18,483 --> 00:15:20,041
How did it go?

232
00:15:20,118 --> 00:15:22,052
I'm dead tired,

233
00:15:22,120 --> 00:15:24,350
but go ahead.
I'm going to bed.

234
00:15:24,422 --> 00:15:27,016
Remember the retired man,
the one with the dog? The nice one?

235
00:15:27,091 --> 00:15:30,492
- He's asked us to do his kitchen over.
- Really?

236
00:15:30,561 --> 00:15:31,653
He thinks we're professionals.

237
00:15:31,729 --> 00:15:33,890
Really? Poor guy!

238
00:15:33,965 --> 00:15:37,423
- Not because of you, Vito.
- Because of me.

239
00:15:37,502 --> 00:15:39,265
So?

240
00:15:39,337 --> 00:15:42,795
So let's add another half-day, sir.

241
00:15:42,874 --> 00:15:44,865
- Four, five hours, not more.
- Yeah.

242
00:15:44,942 --> 00:15:47,877
- That should be enough.
- So how much should we ask for then?

243
00:15:47,945 --> 00:15:49,845
I'm no good at this.

244
00:16:00,324 --> 00:16:02,383
Don't worry, I'll do it.

245
00:16:02,460 --> 00:16:06,021
It's far.
The office is at the port.

246
00:16:06,097 --> 00:16:08,565
Yes?

247
00:16:30,321 --> 00:16:31,788
Careful, Luciano.

248
00:16:31,856 --> 00:16:34,689
Sir, did Luciano tell
you the news?

249
00:16:34,759 --> 00:16:37,159
- What news?
- He's going to be a grandfather.

250
00:16:37,228 --> 00:16:38,923
Congratulations, Luciano!

251
00:16:38,996 --> 00:16:41,157
Yes. Too bad there's no father.

252
00:16:41,232 --> 00:16:42,859
Luciano, come on.

253
00:16:42,934 --> 00:16:46,233
As my wife would say,
that's not necessarily a disadvantage.

254
00:16:46,304 --> 00:16:48,397
You need to introduce me
to your wife.

255
00:16:48,472 --> 00:16:51,339
- Sure.
- Good morning, sir.

256
00:16:51,409 --> 00:16:52,671
Good morning.
How are things going?

257
00:16:52,743 --> 00:16:54,142
Pretty well, I'd say.

258
00:16:54,212 --> 00:16:57,409
