00:39:56,726 --> 00:39:59,490
She said we should've called her,
but I think we did the right thing not to.

510
00:40:01,531 --> 00:40:05,092
Riki, thanks for not asking too many
questions. I appreciate the discretion.

511
00:40:05,168 --> 00:40:07,636
I never liked poking
my nose in other people's shit.

512
00:40:09,239 --> 00:40:11,935
I bought croissants,
but you'll need to make the coffee.

513
00:40:12,008 --> 00:40:13,270
I have to go.

514
00:40:13,343 --> 00:40:15,208
Okay, thanks.

515
00:40:15,278 --> 00:40:17,712
Have a nice day.

516
00:40:17,780 --> 00:40:20,510
If you happen to come this way again,
you're welcome.

517
00:40:20,583 --> 00:40:23,313
- Bye.
- Bye.

518
00:40:47,877 --> 00:40:50,107
Hi, Dad.

519
00:40:53,216 --> 00:40:54,911
Is breakfast included?

520
00:40:54,984 --> 00:40:57,350
Sure, bed and breakfast.

521
00:41:02,659 --> 00:41:05,526
Not much fun
to come home dead tired

522
00:41:05,595 --> 00:41:08,723
and find your asshole
of a father on the couch.

523
00:41:09,866 --> 00:41:11,333
Did you fight?

524
00:41:11,401 --> 00:41:14,302
Yes. Where are the cups?

525
00:41:14,370 --> 00:41:17,134
Is it serious, Dad?

526
00:41:19,075 --> 00:41:20,838
Yes.

527
00:41:20,910 --> 00:41:24,038
Sit down,
I'll get the cups.

528
00:41:27,750 --> 00:41:29,650
Where were you, in Sardinia?

529
00:41:29,719 --> 00:41:32,517
No, in Corsica, near Ajaccio.

530
00:41:32,588 --> 00:41:36,115
- Beautiful.
- Yes, it is.

531
00:41:42,498 --> 00:41:45,990
Now tell me,
does he bring them every morning?

532
00:41:46,069 --> 00:41:49,004
More or less. Why?

533
00:41:49,072 --> 00:41:50,972
No, nothing.

534
00:41:51,040 --> 00:41:53,838
He's nice.

535
00:41:53,910 --> 00:41:55,571
Who would have thought, huh?

536
00:43:43,352 --> 00:43:45,877
Nadia, hi. Forgive me.

537
00:43:45,955 --> 00:43:48,389
I didn't call you.

538
00:43:48,458 --> 00:43:51,791
I disappeared again,

539
00:43:51,861 --> 00:43:55,297
but I'd be really glad
to see you.

540
00:43:55,364 --> 00:43:57,423
Will you call me
when you can?

541
00:43:59,135 --> 00:44:00,762
Bye.

542
00:44:18,821 --> 00:44:21,381
Yes? Good morning.

543
00:44:21,457 --> 00:44:23,425
Good morning, ma'am.
Your husband?

544
00:44:23,493 --> 00:44:25,358
He isn't in.

545
00:44:25,428 --> 00:44:27,589
- Did he find a job?
- No no no.

546
00:44:27,663 --> 00:44:30,291
I'm sorry.
I'll come back tomorrow.

547
00:44:30,366 --> 00:44:33,995
- For a second, I thought that...
- I wish.

548
00:44:34,070 --> 00:44:36,834
You see, ma'am,

549
00:44:36,906 --> 00:44:39,067
I've lived here for 10 years.

550
00:44:39,141 --> 00:44:41,075
My washing machine's broken

551
00:44:41,143 --> 00:44:43,611
and your husband is
the only person

552
00:44:43,679 --> 00:44:47,046
I could ask a favor of.

553
00:44:51,921 --> 00:44:53,786
If you want, I can do it.

554
00:44:53,856 --> 00:44:56,051
No, don't worry about it.

555
00:44:56,125 --> 00:44:58,958
Could I have the... back?

556
00:44:59,028 --> 00:45:01,724
What? Oh, this? Sure.

557
00:45:01,797 --> 00:45:03,788
Thank you.

558
00:45:03,866 --> 00:45:06,733
- Goodbye, ma'am.
- Goodbye.

559
00:45:13,676 --> 00:45:16,042
Dad, leave it!

560
00:45:16,112 --> 00:45:17,943
Oh, I see.

561
00:45:20,016 --> 00:45:23,281
- How pretty you are.
- Thanks.

562
00:45:23,352 --> 00:45:25,980
I'm going to the accountant
this afternoon.

563
00:45:26,055 --> 00:45:27,750
We have to make
some decisions.

564
00:45:27,823 --> 00:45:31,384
They say we should invest
because of taxation problems.

565
00:45:31,460 --> 00:45:33,360
I don't envy you.

566
00:45:34,964 --> 00:45:36,591
Dad...

567
00:45:36,666 --> 00:45:38,691
why don't you give us a hand?

568
00:45:38,768 --> 00:45:40,702
I've never been
a genius at accounting.

569
00:45:40,770 --> 00:45:43,295
Neither have we.

570
00:45:47,677 --> 00:45:49,338
- Will you drive?
- Mm-hmm.

571
00:46:04,360 --> 00:46:07,022
- Michele. Hi.
- Hi.

572
00:46:07,096 --> 00:46:09,656
- How are you?
- Fine.

573
00:46:12,368 --> 00:46:15,064
- Hi, Adele.
- Hi.

574
00:46:16,706 --> 00:46:18,765
- Hi.
- Hi.

575
00:46:24,046 --> 00:46:26,173
Minestrone tonight too?

576
00:46:26,248 --> 00:46:28,375
- I think so.
- Can't you smell it?

577
00:46:31,153 --> 00:46:33,678
- Is he cooking some fried stuff tonight?
- I hope not.

578
00:46:33,756 --> 00:46:37,123
- I need a hand.
- Here.

579
00:46:41,497 --> 00:46:44,625
Dad, I'm sorry,
but we need to set the table.

580
00:46:44,700 --> 00:46:46,258
It's a mess, right?

581
00:46:46,335 --> 00:46:48,200
It's gratifying.

582
00:46:48,270 --> 00:46:51,171
In this chaos,
I almost feel like a genius.

583
00:46:51,240 --> 00:46:53,003
We really suck at this, huh?

584
00:46:53,075 --> 00:46:55,168
I think you've had
some bad advice.

585
00:46:55,244 --> 00:46:56,302
Why?

586
00:46:56,379 --> 00:46:58,006
Before investing
without a reason,

587
00:46:58,080 --> 00:47:01,379
you could do simpler things.

588
00:47:01,450 --> 00:47:04,248
Anyway, I've made a little
financial plan for you.

589
00:47:04,320 --> 00:47:06,754
I'm leaving it here for you.
We can discuss it later.

590
00:47:06,822 --> 00:47:08,050
Of course, with pleasure.

591
00:47:08,124 --> 00:47:10,649
Would you like to come
to the accountant's with us?

592
00:47:10,726 --> 00:47:13,661
Yes, but not today.

593
00:48:35,778 --> 00:48:38,542
Just one?

594
00:48:40,983 --> 00:48:43,645
Now we'll see him again.

595
00:48:43,719 --> 00:48:45,744
Where is he going?

596
00:48:51,093 --> 00:48:53,653
- Hello?
- Did you call him?

597
00:49:15,217 --> 00:49:17,412
Nicola...

598
00:49:17,486 --> 00:49:18,851
Gagliano!

599
00:49:18,921 --> 00:49:21,014
That was the name
of my second mate on the Victoria.

600
00:49:21,090 --> 00:49:24,958
Nicola Gagliano.

601
00:49:48,484 --> 00:49:51,112
That's fine. If that's okay,
I'll give them a call.

602
00:49:51,187 --> 00:49:53,587
Yes, don't worry.

603
00:49:53,656 --> 00:49:56,181
You too, thanks.

604
00:49:56,258 --> 00:49:58,021
Goodbye for now.

605
00:49:58,093 --> 00:50:00,118
Mr. Rinaldi called.

606
00:50:00,196 --> 00:50:02,824
He wants you to call
him back. It's urgent.

607
00:50:02,898 --> 00:50:06,390
Rinaldi, what a fucking bore!
Okay, I'll call him,

608
00:50:06,468 --> 00:50:10,131
then if you like
we can go for a drink.

609
00:50:10,206 --> 00:50:12,640
I can't this evening.
I have to go somewhere.

610
00:50:15,411 --> 00:50:16,901
I'll take you if you like.

611
00:50:16,979 --> 00:50:19,140
No, thanks. Really.

612
00:50:20,783 --> 00:50:23,013
All right,
see you tomorrow then.

613
00:50:23,085 --> 00:50:25,349
Tomorrow is Saturday.

614
00:50:25,421 --> 00:50:27,252
You're right.

615
00:50:29,491 --> 00:50:31,049
You're free to go then.

616
00:50:31,126 --> 00:50:33,253
Thanks.
Have a nice evening.

617
00:50:51,280 --> 00:50:54,249
Good evening.
Banchi Square.

618
00:51:21,744 --> 00:51:24,474
We thought the color
had faded completely,

619
00:51:24,546 --> 00:51:28,448
but actually
it's been left in sinopia.

620
00:51:28,517 --> 00:51:31,884
It's as if he had to stop
at a certain point.

621
00:51:31,954 --> 00:51:33,615
Maybe his illness.

622
00:51:33,689 --> 00:51:35,350
Elsa, you're back!

623
00:51:35,424 --> 00:51:37,688
- Professor.
- Good evening, Elsa.

624
00:51:37,760 --> 00:51:41,321
Look! Isn't it marvelous?

625
00:51:50,372 --> 00:51:54,206
Congratulations.
Wonderful intuition.

626
00:51:54,276 --> 00:51:56,744
The brushwork
and the colors,

627
00:51:56,812 --> 00:51:58,837
even the angel's face
has a lot in common

628
00:51:58,914 --> 00:52:00,848
with his female figures.

629
00:52:00,916 --> 00:52:03,441
But I think it's really the landscape

630
00:52:03,519 --> 00:52:06,113
- that eliminates all doubt.
- It's the light, isn't it?

631
00:52:07,589 --> 00:52:11,252
It's the light of your Boniforte.

632
00:52:11,327 --> 00:52:13,625
Good job.

633
00:52:13,696 --> 00:52:17,223
Elsa, we're going to have a drink,

634
00:52:17,299 --> 00:52:19,494
and we've convinced
the professor to join us.

635
00:52:19,568 --> 00:52:21,160
What are you doing?

636
00:52:21,236 --> 00:52:23,204
I'd like to stay
for a moment.

637
00:52:23,272 --> 00:52:25,763
- Are you going
to the usual bar?
- Come on, will you join us?

638
00:52:25,841 --> 00:52:28,867
Will you lock up?
You have the keys, anyway.

639
00:52:28,944 --> 00:52:31,412
- Yes.
- Enjoy this moment. You deserve it.

640
00:54:20,789 --> 00:54:23,087
I'm really ashamed
of what happened yesterday.

641
00:54:25,561 --> 00:54:28,223
Me too.

642
00:54:28,297 --> 00:54:30,595
I thought things could go back
to the way they were,

643
00:54:30,666 --> 00:54:34,534
but it's not true.
I realized it's a mistake to look back.

644
00:54:37,372 --> 00:54:40,034
I don't even know
how we got where we are.

645
00:54:43,946 --> 00:54:46,107
I thought nothing
could separate us.

646
00:54:46,181 --> 00:54:48,615
It's not true.

647
00:54:51,420 --> 00:54:54,116
I can't lose you, Elsa.

648
00:54:57,192 --> 00:54:59,319
When I look ahead lately,
I only see endless strain,

649
00:54:59,394 --> 00:55:01,555
an unbelievable strain.

650
00:55:01,630 --> 00:55:03,598
We have to take it from here.

651
00:55:03,665 --> 00:55:06,395
I'll come up with something.
I'll start from scratch...

652
00:55:06,468 --> 00:55:08,732
I don't care...
but not without you.

653
00:55:08,804 --> 00:55:10,567
Without you,
I'm going nowhere.

654
00:55:28,056 --> 00:55:29,717
You arrived right
when I was thinking

655
00:55:29,791 --> 00:55:32,589
that the only thing I wanted
was to have you here.

656
00:55:35,097 --> 00:55:37,088
It is you, right?

657
00:55:37,166 --> 00:55:38,827
It's me, Elsa.

658
00:55:38,901 --> 00:55:41,563
Unfortunately, it's really me.

659
00:55:45,107 --> 00:55:47,405
Me too.

